This solution computes the stage value (sum) and carry-out using Boolean expressions of the [full adder circuit][1] <br> The circuit for the full adder is below.
![Full Adder circuit][2]
<br>
The expressions are.

                 S     = A xor B xor C_in
                 C_out = A.B + C_in. (A xor B)

The inputs are padded to the same size to emulate a hardware-adder with inputs of the same size.

    string addBinary(string a, string b) {
        // Pad to same length
        if (a.size()> b.size())
                 b.insert(b.begin(), a.size()-b.size(), '0');
        else
                 a.insert(a.begin(), b.size()-a.size(), '0');
        int len = a.size();
        bool carry_out= false, sum= false;
        string res(len, '0'); // all zero
        for (int i=len-1; i>=0 ; --i) {
                bool ai = a[i]-'0'== 1; 
                bool bi = b[i]-'0'== 1;
                // Full adder sum = (A xor B xor C_in)
                sum = ai != bi != carry_out ;
                // Full adder C_out =  (A.B + C_in. (A xor B))
                carry_out =  ai && bi || (carry_out && (ai != bi)) ; 
                if (sum) res[i] = '1';
        }
        if (carry_out)  // carry over at end
                res= "1" + res;
        return res;
    }

Note I have used boolean xor operator (i.e. != operator) instead of bit-wise xor ( ^ operator)


  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adder_%28electronics%29#Full_adder
  [2]: http://www.cs.iit.edu/~cs561/cs350/ADDER/full_adder.jpg

