##### **Approach:**
1. Intinilize The **i from 0** and **j from n-1**
2. we are going to check each time that what number at i and number at j makes up
3. if it is less than target we **increment i**
4. if it is greater than target we **decrement j**

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> twoSum(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        vector <int> ans; // Answer Array
        int i = 0, j = nums.size() - 1; // Initilize Two Pointers
        while (i < j) {
            if (nums[i] + nums[j] < target) ++i;
            else if (nums[i] + nums[j] > target) --j;
            else {
                ans.push_back(i+1);
                ans.push_back(j+1);
                break;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

