# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Create two pointers where one points at the first index in the array and the other points at the second index. 
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d1bf7a1b-14d2-4c20-95fb-f0e28e8ef04c_1692158325.868738.png)

If the sum of the values at the pointers is less than the target, shift both pointers over one. 
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ab1f29a8-b028-4831-9cb4-d465f80cf8b3_1692158387.3140357.png)

If the values summed are greater, shift the first pointer left one. 
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0729c0f4-9453-4fec-bb8b-cce8c3274bfe_1692158455.6069474.png)

