We use a very important property here that the array is sorted...
Now we initialize two pointers, i and j, one being at start of the array and other being at the end...
If the sum of these two elements is smaller than the target, we know that no element on left of i can sum with j to give us target, hence we move i forward...
Similarly if sum of these two elements is greater than the target, we know that no element on right of j can sum with i to give us target, hence we j backward...
If we reach target, we simply return these index added by 1...

