##### Two pointer technique:-
* We can exploit the sorted property of an array.
* Let's say for indices` i` & `j` such that` i<j,`
* if sum of elements `nums[i]+nums[j] == target, `then we are done
* else check whether `nums[i]+nums[j] > target,` then last element has to be removed to reduce the value of sum` (j--).`
* similarly if `nums[i]+nums[j] < target`, we have to add little to increase the sum `(i++).`

*Time Complexity: O (n)
Space Complexity: O (1)*

